# DockerComms v1.0 - Implementation Rules

Reference: SPEC.md (protocol), ARCH.md (architecture). This is patent-bound open source. Zero bugs. Zero security flaws.

## Security (Non-Negotiable)

- NEVER write payload to disk before signature verification (verify-before-materialize)
- ALWAYS validate signed digest equals manifest digest
- Path traversal defense: filename is basename only (SanitizeFilename)
- Constant-time comparison for digests/hashes where applicable
- Hard limits: MaxChunks, MaxTotalBytes

## Code Quality

- Go 1.23+
- gofmt -s compliant
- NO panic() outside main()
- NO os.Exit() outside main() (return ExitError; main handles)
- NO init() functions
- NO global mutable state
- NO ignored errors (_ = something() without justification)
- NO emojis in code/docs
- NO TODO comments (create issues)
- NO commented-out code
- Function length < 50 lines; cyclomatic complexity < 15

## Error Handling

```go
if err != nil {
    return fmt.Errorf("contextual operation: %w", err)
}
f, err := os.Open(path)
if err != nil { return err }
defer f.Close()
```

## Tag Grammar (SPEC.md)

- inbox-<recipient_tag>-<YYYYMMDD>-<sid8>-<mid8>
- receipt-<hexDigest12>-<ts>-<rand>
- bundle-<hexDigest12>-<ts>-<rand>
- recipient_tag = lower(base32hex(sha256(recipient)))[:26]
- NO slashes, NO colons in tag; max 128 chars

## Testing

- Unit tests for every package
- go test -race ./... must pass
- Chunking: boundary conditions, round-trip
- OCI: mock or integration
- Crypto: tampered data must fail

## Prohibited

- interface{} without type assertion
- json.Marshal without error handling
- HTTP without timeout/context
- File ops without defer Close
- String concat in loops (use strings.Builder)
- Hardcoded credentials
